collection

Interface Set<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of the elements stored in this collection.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Bag<E>, Collection<E>, Iterable<E>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    NavigableSet<E>, SortedSet<E>

    public interface Set<E>
extends Bag<E>
    Based on the mathematical definition of a set. Basically acts like a bag, but overrides equals and hashcode methods. Order does not matter, and replacement is not allowed. Adds behavior to return a subSet.
    Author:
    Jacob Malter
